This project develops the modeling and simulation tools, physics-based models, virtual and scaled radio frequency (RF) hardware and software prototypes to validate
and mature adaptive multi-function resource management, tracking and discrimination algorithms, and radar sensor technologies in support of Long Range Precision
Fires.

 Work in this Project complements Program Element (PE) 0602141A (Lethality Technology) / Project CG4 (Advanced Radar Concepts and Technologies).

 The cited research is consistent with the Under Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering priority focus areas and the Army Modernization Strategy.

